codex
For the shipped in-world `GroundScene`, the camera is corrected every draw. For 
pre-game/backdrop/UI-owned 3D, the stale consumer is more plausible: UI root/layout and any UI-owned 
camera/widget dimensions only update when the root is repacked. I’m ready to summarize by question.
codex
**1. 3D World Scene Render Target**

The in-world scene does render through `PostProcessingEffectsManager` when post effects are enabled.

`CuiIoWin::draw()` wraps scene drawing with:
- `PostProcessingEffectsManager::preSceneRender()` before `IoWin::draw()` at 
`src/engine/client/library/clientUserInterface/src/shared/core/CuiIoWin.cpp:205-208`
- `PostProcessingEffectsManager::postSceneRender()` after bloom at 
`src/engine/client/library/clientUserInterface/src/shared/core/CuiIoWin.cpp:210-211`

`PostProcessingEffectsManager::preSceneRender()` binds `ms_primaryBuffer` as the render target at 
`src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/PostProcessingEffectsManager.cpp:193-195`, and 
immediately checks it against live `Graphics::getCurrentRenderTargetWidth/Height()` in Debug at 
`PostProcessingEffectsManager.cpp:196-197`.

That primary buffer is on the device-restored path:
- callback registration: `PostProcessingEffectsManager.cpp:107-109`
- full-size RT fetch from `Graphics::getFrameBufferMaxWidth/Height()`: 
`PostProcessingEffectsManager.cpp:137-143`
- release on lost: `PostProcessingEffectsManager.cpp:150-168`

I did not find another full-screen scene RT allocated once and missed by resize. Repo-wide 
`TCF_renderTarget` hits are only:
- `PostProcessingEffectsManager` full-size primary/secondary/tertiary: 
`PostProcessingEffectsManager.cpp:141-143`
- `Bloom` quarter-size buffers: 
`src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Bloom.cpp:156-166`

`Bloom` is also on device-restored:
- callback registration: `Bloom.cpp:122-125`
- quarter-size re-fetch from `Graphics::getFrameBufferMaxWidth/Height()`: `Bloom.cpp:154-166`

So the fixed-size scene-RT hypothesis is not supported by the source I read. The primary scene RT 
should be recreated to the new size.

**2. Viewport**

The in-world `GroundScene` viewport is live-size based each frame.

`GroundScene::draw()` does:
- full viewport from live `Graphics::getCurrentRenderTargetWidth/Height()`: 
`src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/scene/GroundScene.cpp:2289`
- current camera viewport from the same live dimensions: `GroundScene.cpp:2299` and 
`GroundScene.cpp:2302`
- restores full viewport after world/shadow rendering: `GroundScene.cpp:2353`

`Camera::setViewport()` stores the passed dimensions and calls `setup()` at 
`src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/Camera.cpp:297-309`. `Camera::renderScene()` 
pushes that camera viewport into graphics at `Camera.cpp:636-640`.

The D3D11 plugin also sets a per-frame full backbuffer viewport from its own `ms_width/ms_height` in 
`Direct3d11_Device::beginScene()` at 
`src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_Device.cpp:923-957`. Those fields are 
updated after `ResizeBuffers` at `Direct3d11_Device.cpp:1223-1234`.

Conclusion: for `GroundScene`, viewport/projection is not cached at install-time; it re-reads the 
live `Graphics` size each draw. If in-world still crops after `Graphics::resize`, the stale artifact 
is less likely to be `GroundScene` camera viewport and more likely a D3D11 state/constant not 
reflecting the resize despite `setViewport` calls, or a path outside `GroundScene`.

**3. UI Layout**

The UI root is sized once at install, and normal `Graphics::resize()` does not re-layout it.

Install-time sizing:
- root page set to current render target size: 
`src/engine/client/library/clientUserInterface/src/shared/core/CuiManager.cpp:448`
- root children packed immediately after: `CuiManager.cpp:449`
- root page installed into `UIManager`: `CuiManager.cpp:451`

The resize/reflow API exists:
- `CuiManager::setSize(int width, int height)` sets root page size and `ForcePackChildren()`: 
`CuiManager.cpp:1368-1375`
- it also resets the dead zone: `CuiManager.cpp:1377-1378`

But `Graphics::resize()` only updates graphics globals and calls `ms_api->resize`; it does not call 
`CuiManager::setSize`: `src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:602-607`.

The only call to `CuiManager::setSize(newWidth, newHeight)` I found is the Qt widget wrapper resize 
path:
- camera viewport/FOV update loop: 
`src/game/client/library/swgClientQtWidgets/src/win32/GameWidget.cpp:1316-1328`
- `Graphics::resize(newWidth, newHeight)`: `GameWidget.cpp:1331-1332`
- `CuiManager::setSize(newWidth, newHeight)`: `GameWidget.cpp:1334-1335`

The normal Win32 gl11 `displayModeChanged()` path queues/applies only `Graphics::resize()`:
- queue request from client rect: `Graphics.cpp:419-445`
- apply in `Graphics::beginScene()`: `Graphics.cpp:1022-1034`

No `CuiManager::setSize()` bridge exists there. That is a concrete stale consumer: 
`UIManager::GetRootPage()` remains at the old install-time size unless the Qt wrapper path or some 
external caller invokes `CuiManager::setSize`.

Also relevant: `CuiManager::render()` resets graphics viewport to live size at `CuiManager.cpp:818`, 
then renders the UI root at `CuiManager.cpp:852`. `UIManager::Render()` only renders the current 
root page; it does not resize/repack it at 
`src/external/3rd/library/ui/src/win32/UIManager.cpp:558-563`.

There is a UI-library `UIManager::SetSize()` helper that packs and sets the root page at 
`UIManager.cpp:544-552`, but the client path uses `CuiManager::setSize()`, and neither is called 
from the Win32 gl11 resize path.

`CutScene` has an existing resolution-change path, but it only calls `Graphics::resize()` at 
